{"action":"patch","name":"supabase-patterns","old_string":"## Pitfalls (Cross-Cutting)","new_string":"### Section J: Deep-Merge for Partial Content Overrides

When a content provider loads defaults from JSON files and overlays Supabase overrides, partial overrides MUST deep-merge — a shallow replace wipes out fields that the override JSON doesn't include.

**The bug pattern:**
```typescript
// WRONG — shallow merge replaces the entire nested object
const merged = { ...defaults, ...overrides }
// If overrides.hero has only `title`, all other hero fields (subtitle, cta, image) disappear

// CORRECT — recursive deep merge preserves unspecified fields
function deepMerge(target: any, source: any): any {
  const result = { ...target }
  for (const key of Object.keys(source)) {
    if (
      source[key] && typeof source[key] === 'object' && !Array.isArray(source[key]) &&
      target[key] && typeof target[key] === 'object' && !Array.isArray(target[key])
    ) {
      result[key] = deepMerge(target[key], source[key])
    } else {
      result[key] = source[key]
    }
  }
  return result
}
```

**Also applies to the `get()` helper:**
```typescript
// WRONG — returns override value directly, losing sibling fields
get(path: string) {
  return deepGet(overrides, path) ?? deepGet(defaults, path)
}

// CORRECT — merges override at the path level
get(path: string) {
  const base = deepGet(defaults, path)
  const over = deepGet(overrides, path)
  if (!over) return base
  if (typeof base === 'object' && typeof over === 'object' && !Array.isArray(base)) {
    return deepMerge(base, over)
  }
  return over ?? base
}
```

**Symptom:** Admin edits one field in a section → other fields in that section revert to empty/undefined on next page load. Sections disappear after client-side hydration because the override JSON only has the edited fields.

**Real incident (El Viajero):** Editing hero slides in admin → kits carousel section vanished because the Supabase override JSON had no `promociones` key, and the shallow merge replaced the entire content object with the partial override.

